Where can you find data about Conflicts?
====================================================

[Georeferenced Event Dataset - UCDP](http://ucdp.uu.se/): A conflict, both state-based and non-state, is deemed to be active if there are at least 25 battle-related deaths per calendar year in one of the conflict's dyads.

[Militarized Interstate Dispute](http://www.correlatesofwar.org/data-sets/MIDs):information about conflicts in which one or more states threaten, display, or use force against one or more other states 

[Armed Conflict Location and Event Data Project)](https://www.acleddata.com/data/): This data set codes the dates and locations of all reported political violence and protest events in over 60 developing countries

